programme.desc: This concert at the Waldbühne in Berlin celebrates the legacy of Wagner and his most famous successor, Richard Strauss. programme.title: Concerts In a Palace
programme.desc: This episode of Concerts in a Palace is the second in a series of six that was recorded in 1999 at the wonderful 18th-century baroque castle Schloß Heidecksburg in Rudolstadt, Germany. Discover the Toulouse Chamber Orchestra perform Edvard Grieg's Holberg Suite, Op. 40(n)

programme.title: Amante Segreto
programme.desc: This wonderful concert brings you a wonderful and varied programme centered around the human voice and the harp. As part of the 'Festival de Saintes' 2014, soprano Céline Scheen and harpist Giovanna Pessi present a beautiful concert of stunning early repertoire at the impressive Abbaye aux Dames.(n)

programme.title: Beethoven
programme.desc: Ta-ta-ta-taa': quite possibly the most famous opening sequence, to one of the most famous symphonies ever written. It has become impossible to think of concert halls today without Beethoven's 'Fifth', but for a symphony this popular it had a rather disastrous opening night(n)

programme.title: Mozart
programme.desc: Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart's opera about Figaro, who would like to marry his Susanna but is blocked in his intentions by his employer the Count, has fascinated audiences throughout the centuries. This broadcast shows the recitative and Count Almaviva's aria.(n)

programme.title: Revueltas
programme.desc: All of the compositions Mexican Silvestre Revueltas wrote in the short span of his life were full of energy and humor. He was a close friend of Carlos Chávez, another great Mexican name in music, and it was Chávez that in 1929 convinced him to come back to Mexico(n)

programme.title: Dvorak
programme.desc: When Antonin Dvorák was elected honourary member of the Royal Philharmonic Society in London in 1884 and invited to write a symphony, the composer was up to the task. He was full of fresh admiration for Brahms' third symphony and he had just been planning to start on a new composition himself(n)

programme.title: Elliott Carter
programme.desc: Pierre-Laurent Aimard, the French specialist for classical and avantgarde music plays 'Matribute', 'Two Diversions' and 'Caténaires' by Elliott Carter (1908-2012). Recorded at the Akademie der Schönen Künste in Munich(n)

programme.title: Liszt
programme.desc: This work forms part of Franz Liszt's 'Années de pèlerinage', a musical journey accompanying the composer's travels with his beloved Marie d'Agoult. Where the first set focused on describing natural scenery, the pieces in this second set describe the artworks Liszt discovers(n)

programme.title: Mozart
programme.desc: Così fan tutte' not only boasts the most beautiful music Mozart ever wrote for an opera, but it's also the most perfect ensemble opera ever. Apart from its wonderful arias, the opera contains a range of brilliant duets, terzets, and quartets(n)

programme.title: Pärt
programme.desc: Born through the friendship between three families (Capuçon, Chalmin and Scapolan), the Bel Air Festival was, for 15 years, a unique place to share, to meet and exchange between musicians coming from all around the globe(n)

programme.title: Concerts In Palace
programme.desc: This episode of Concerts in Palace is the third in a series of six that was recorded in 1999 at the wonderful 18th-century baroque castle Schloß Heidecksburg in Rudolstadt, Germany(n)

programme.title: Ullrich Böhme Plays Organ Works By Bach
programme.desc: The German organist Ullrich Böhme performs various organ works by J. S. Bach at St. Thomas Church in Leipzig. On the program are five chorales from Orgelbüchlein; the plays Jesu meine Freude, Nun Danket alle Gott, Jesu bleibet meine freude, and Vor deinen Thron tret ich hiermit(n)

programme.title: Mahler
programme.desc: Aufersteh'n, ja aufersteh'n wirst du, mein Herz in einem Nu! Was du geschlagen, zu Gott wird es dich tragen! The final chorus of Mahler's beautiful and impressive second symphony never fails to move its listeners(n)

programme.title: Massenet
programme.desc: Jules Massenet was one of the most celebrated opera composers of his day, which earned him much money and fame. Nowadays, he is most remembered because of his operas Manon and Werther, and of course this violin solo from his opera Thäis(n)

programme.title: Bartók
programme.desc: In 1943, after his health had deteriorated over a very short period of time, Béla Bartók was diagnosed with leukaemia. Almost three years earlier he had escaped World War II and left Europe for the United States, but there he felt isolated artistically and had financial problems on top of that(n)

programme.title: Franz Liszt Piano Competition
programme.desc: Saskia Giorgini began her piano studies at the Accademia Pianistica in Imola with Franco Scala, Louis Lortie and Michel Dalberto, among others. She is currently continuing her studies at the Mozarteum in Salzburg with Enrico Pace and Pavel Gililov(n)

programme.title: Mozart
programme.desc: From the Barockschloss in Rammenau the Gewandhaus-Quartett plays Mozart's String Quartet No. 19 in C-major, KV. 465. In this performance, it consists of Frank Michael Erben (1st violin), Conrad Suske (2nd violin), Volker Metz (viola), Jürnjakob Timm (cello) and Steffen Adelmann (doublebass)(n)

programme.title: Tchaikovsky
programme.desc: Swan Lake is one of the most loved of all classical ballets and one of the most popular in the Royal Ballet repertory. It has that magical combination of Tchaikovsky's music, a compelling story of tragic romance(n)

programme.title: Four Seasons Of Buenos Aires
programme.desc: Invierno Porteño is part of a four-movement cycle named Las cuatro estaciones porteñas or Four Buenos Aires Seasons which, as the name suggests, is a tribute to the tango of Buenos Aires and also to the baroque composer Antonio Vivaldi(n)

programme.title: Beethoven
programme.desc: Beethoven met Goethe but was disappointed by his personality, had an eventful love life and wrote the famous letter to his anonymous 'Unsterbliche Geliebte' (Immortal Beloved) and also tried to interfere in the life of his youngest brother, who had an affair with one of the maids(n)

programme.title: Rias Kammerchor
programme.desc: The German hymn 'Jesu, meine Freude' was composed by Johann Franck in 1650. Johann Sebastian Bach used this hymn for his motet and his prelude for choir and organ, which he composed for a funeral. The prelude can be found in his 'Orgelbüchlein', a volumewhich contains 46 preludes for organ(n)

programme.title: Celebrating Mozart
programme.desc: An unmatchable highlight of the Mozart year is the Festkonzert from Salzburg. A Gala concert with the Wiener Philharmoniker under Riccardo Muti and stars of the highest calibre such as Thomas Hampson (baritone), Gidon Kremer (violin), Yuri Bashmet (viola) and Mitsuko Uchida (piano)(n)

programme.title: The Red Ribbon Celebration Concert 2015
programme.desc: The Life Ball in Vienna is one of the biggest fundraising events in support of those living with HIV or AIDS. Part of the event is the Red Ribbon Celebration Concert, staged in the Burgtheater. In 2015, its "Building Bridges for Peace" concert assembled a line-up of biggest international stars(n)

programme.title: The Changing Seasons
programme.desc: The Netherlands Chamber Orchestra commissioned violinist Tim Kliphuis, internationally known for his genre-crossing approach to music, to write a new version of Antonio Vivaldi's 'Four Seasons'. Kliphuis choose to take improvisation as his starting point(n)

programme.title: In Search Of Chopin
programme.desc: His grave in Paris remains a place of pilgrimage and his music continues to sell out concert halls worldwide – but who exactly was this man who was terrified of public performance, who fled his Polish homeland for Paris never to return, took up with the most notorious transvestite in France.(n)

programme.title: Corelli
programme.desc: The Italian violinist and composer Arcangelo Corelli, born in Rome in 1653, decided to study in Bologna, the cultural capital of those days. After enjoying success as a violinist, he decided to compose his own violin sonatas. This also turned out a success, and he decided to take on pupils(n)

programme.title: Chopin
programme.desc: The Étude No. 3, nicknamed "Tristesse", is actually a study for solo piano by Frédéric Chopin, written in 1832. The piece was published as the third of his Études Op. 10. It is a slow study for polyphonic and legato playing(n)

programme.title: Bach
programme.desc: Thanks to his antics at the piano, his unquestionable love for the works of Johann Sebastian Bach, and his unbelievable technique, it is only logical that the young French pianist David Fray has often been compared to pianist Glenn Gould(n)

programme.title: Beethoven
programme.desc: For his 65th birthday, Daniel Barenboim has completed a cycle of Beethoven's piano concertos. Recorded live at the prestigious Klavier-Festival Ruhr in 2007, this recording reflects both a very individual and special reading of Beethoven's music and the artist's life-long dedication to the composer(n)

programme.title: Márquez
programme.desc: Proof that music can change lives can be found with the Fundación del Estado para el Sistema Nacional de las Orquestas Juveniles e Infantiles de Venezuela, also known as El Sistema. This network of about 125 youth orchestras enables children from the slums of Venezuela to learn to play an.(n)

programme.title: Vivaldi
programme.desc: The Staatskapelle Dresden, under direction of Giuseppe Sinopoli, performs Antonio Vivaldi's 'Concerto di Dresda'(n)

programme.title: La Dolce Vita
programme.desc: La Dolce Vita', 'Cinema Paradiso': two classics of Italian cinema that are not only loved for their storytelling, but also for their matchless music. And when that gorgeous music is performed by the New York Philharmonic and vocalists Josh Groban, Renée Fleming, and violinist Joshua Bell(n)

programme.title: IVC Masterclass
programme.desc: The International Vocal Competition's-Hertogenbosch (IVC) was founded in 1954. Since then, it has been the Netherlands' only international classical vocal competition featuring two categories: oratorio and Lied(n)

programme.title: Beethoven
programme.desc: The year 1812 was a busy year for the well-known but deaf composer Ludwig van Beethoven. At last, Beethoven got the chance to meet that other famous German, Johann Wolfgang von Goethe, but Goethe's personality proved a disappointed to Beethoven(n)

programme.title: Four Seasons Of Buenos Aires
programme.desc: Verano porteño was first heard as part of the recorded incidental music for a theater production in Buenos Aires in August 1965; Piazzolla and his quintet premiered the complete suite on May 19, 1970, at the Teatro Regina in Buenos Aires(n)

programme.title: Dvorák
programme.desc: The year 1878 was an important one for Czech composer Antonin Dvorák. Thanks to his friend Johannes Brahms his works were first published in Germany, increasing his reputation and earning him more composition assigments(n)

programme.title: Verdi
programme.desc: "La Forza del Destino" (1862) is one of Giuseppe Verdi's most tragic operas. It deals with the impossible love of Donna Leonora, the daughter of the Marquis of Calatrava, and Don Alvaro, a nobleman with Indian blood(n)

programme.title: Mahler
programme.desc: Gustav Mahler's third symphony is, with its unequalled length of approximately 95 minutes, an exciting, mysterious, overbearing and moving piece. In the six parts of this marvellous symphony, Mahler expresses his musical vision on nature, and the place of mankind in nature(n)

programme.title: Mozart
programme.desc: When Mozart and his wife made a stopover in Linz on their trip from Vienna to Salzburg in 1783 and the local count found out about this, the composer was invited to perform a concert. Mozart of course could not refuse, but had a problem: he had not brought a single symphony with him(n)

programme.title: Shostakovich
programme.desc: On the eve of the 300th anniversary, the city of Saint Petersburg, the Russian 'window to Europe', celebrated its jubilee with a great musical spectacle. The crème de la crème of Russia's classical music scene came together in St(n)

programme.desc: Um grupo de operários percebe que a administração está a roubar máquinas e matérias-primas da sua própria fábrica. Quando se organizam são forçados, como retaliação, a permanecer nos seus postos sem nada que fazer, enquanto negoceiam os despedimentos(n)

programme.title: Nenhum Nome
programme.desc: Um homem sofre um grave acidente de carro e é internado na unidade de queimados de um hospital. A enfermeira responsável pela sua reabilitação está grávida de seis meses, um facto que vai ajudar a fortalecer aquela relação, aparentemente impessoal(n)

programme.title: Olhares Lugares
programme.desc: Um documentário sobre a viagem da cineasta Agnès Varda e JR, seu fã de longa data, icónico fotógrafo e muralista, através da França rural. Ambos partilham uma vida apaixonada pelas imagens, como são criadas, exibidas e partilhadas(n)

programme.title: King in the Wilderness
programme.desc: Um olhar sobre os últimos anos de vida de Martin Luther King Jr(n)

programme.title: A Divina Comédia

programme.title: Uma Mulher Fantástica
programme.desc: Marina é uma jovem transgénero que vive um grande amor com Orlando, 20 anos mais velho, longe dos olhares alheios. Mas quando ele morre de repente, Marina é alvo da hostilidade dos familiares de Orlando, que rejeitam tudo o que ela representa(n)

programme.title: Chaco

programme.title: Curtas às Quartas

programme.title: Yours In Sisterhood

programme.title: Trinta Lumes

programme.title: Rasto de Violência

programme.title: Ventos de Outubro
programme.desc: Helen Matthews é uma médica de luto que viaja até uma ilha onde costumava passar bons momentos com o marido. Um homem misterioso e ferido surge na sua cabana e pede-lhe ajuda. O problema surge quando o assassino aparece para finalizar o trabalho(n)

programme.title: O Labirinto
programme.desc: Deixada a tomar conta do irmão bebé, a jovem Sarah deseja que ele seja levado para um mundo imaginário habitado por criaturas místicas. Quando percebe que o seu desejo se realizou, Sarah terá de percorrer o labirinto do rei Goblin para salvar o irmão(n)

programme.title: No Mesmo Tom

programme.title: Wildlike

programme.title: A Invasão

programme.title: Palavrões

Além disso, têm assassinos no seu encalce(n)

programme.title: Os Pobres Anos Dourados

No entanto, após um caso com uma atraente desconhecida, torna-se o principal suspeito do seu desaparecimento e dum golpe milionário(n)
